HEADWORD: Ropery
<hw>Rop"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place
where ropes are made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tricks deserving the halter; roguery.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Saucy merchant . . . so full of his
<xex>ropery</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rope's-end</ent>⟦br⟧
